{
  "title": "Designing Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to create cron-driven tasks in a FastAPI application running on Python 3.12+, utilizing the Apscheduler library for task scheduling.",

  "key_points": [
    "Install necessary dependencies: FastAPI, Apscheduler, and an ASGI server like Hypercorn.",
    "Create a new FastAPI instance and define your API endpoints.",
    "Define the scheduled task function that will be executed by Apscheduler.",
    "Initialize and configure Apscheduler with the FastAPI application instance.",
    "Register the scheduled task with Apscheduler using an interval, when to start, and timezone settings.",
    "Run the FastAPI app with ASGI, making sure the Apscheduler extension is included.",
    "Access the API endpoints for executing, pausing, resuming, or removing scheduled tasks."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\n# Install dependencies\n\n$ pip install fastapi apscheduler hypercorn\n\nimport asyncio\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\nfrom apscheduler.schedulers.asyncio import AsyncIOScheduler\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nscheduler = AsyncIOScheduler()\n\ndef task():\n    # Your scheduled task code here\n\n# Register the task with Apscheduler\n\nscheduler.add_interval_job(task, seconds=60)\n\nscheduler.start()\n\nasynchronio.run(app.fastapi_app)\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python version: 3.12+"
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Make sure you have ASGI support in your web server to run FastAPI.",
    "For more complex scheduling needs, consider using Apscheduler's other features like cron expressions and one-time jobs."
  ]
}
